Great professor. Took her intro to historical studies course in the summer and although it was packed with info and assignments, it was to be expected. She did however take it easy on us and the TAs were quite generous. She does have a tendency to go on for a while without stops so be prepared to write/type fast. Seems to be knowledgeable, 4/5.

rComments: She is a great professor, very approachable outside of class and knowledgeable. She picked out long readings but they were interesting. I can't say much about her marking, as TAs did the marking, but the assignments were straight-forward. Her exam was average difficulty, MCQs were a bit challenging. Overall, I would recommend her.
